<div class=3D"cue-carousel">
<ol class=3D"slider-wrapper">
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-856">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> Find the n<sup>th </sup>term of the arithmet=
ic sequence -5, -7/2, -2, ....</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>The given sequence is -5, -7/2, -2, ...</p>
<p>Here, the first term is a =3D -5, and the common difference is, d =3D -(=
7/2) - (-5) =3D -2 - (-7/2) =3D ... =3D 3/2.</p>
<p>The n<sup>th</sup> term of an arithmetic sequence is given by</p>
<p>a<sub>n</sub> =3D a<sub>1</sub> + (n=E2=88=921)d</p>
<p>a<sub>n</sub> =3D -5 +(n - 1) (3/2)</p>
<p>=3D -5+ (3/2)n - 3/2</p>
<p>=3D 3n/2 - 13/2</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The n<sup>th</sup> term of the given arithmetic=
 sequence is, a<sub>n</sub> =3D 3n/2 - 13/2.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-294">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> Which term of the arithmetic sequence -3, -8=
, -13, -18,... is -248?</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>The given arithmetic sequence is -3, -8, -13, -18,...</p>
<p>The first term is, a =3D -3</p>
<p>The common difference is, d =3D -8 - (-3) =3D -13 - (-8) =3D ... =3D -5.=
</p>
<p>It is given that the n<sup>th</sup> term is, a<sub>n</sub> =3D -248.</p>
<p>Substitute all these values in the n<sup>th</sup> term of an arithmetic =
sequence formula,</p>
<p>a<sub>n</sub> =3D a<sub>1</sub> + (n=E2=88=921)d<br>
	=E2=87=92 -248 =3D -3 + (-5)(n - 1)<br>
	=E2=87=92 -248 =3D -3 -5n + 5<br>
	=E2=87=92 -248 =3D 2 - 5n<br>
	=E2=87=92 -250 =3D -5n<br>
	=E2=87=92 n =3D 50</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> -248 is the 50<sup>th</sup> term of the given s=
equence.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-321">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 3:</strong> Find the sum of the arithmetic sequence -3, =
-8, -13, -18,.., -248.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>This sequence is the same as the one that is given in <strong>Example 2<=
/strong>.</p>
<p>There we found that a =3D -3, d =3D -5, and n =3D 50.</p>
<p>So we have to find the sum of the 50 terms of the given arithmetic serie=
s.</p>
<p>S<sub>n</sub> =3D n/2[a<sub>1</sub> + a<sub>n</sub>]</p>
<p>S<sub>50</sub> =3D [50 (-3 - 248)]/2 =3D -6275</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The sum of the given arithmetic sequence is -62=
75.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
