d-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>=
A sequence of numbers in which every term (except the first term) is obtain=
ed by adding a constant number to the previous term is called an <strong>ar=
ithmetic sequence</strong>. For example, 1, 3, 5, 7, ... is an arithmetic s=
equence as every term is obtained by adding 2 (a constant number) to its pr=
evious term.</p><ul>
</ul></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" ite=
