" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>If the d=
ifference between every two consecutive terms of a sequence is the same the=
n it is an arithmetic sequence. For example, 3, 8, 13, 18 ... is arithmetic=
 because the consecutive terms have a fixed difference.</p><ul>
