nswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><d=
iv itemprop=3D"text"><p>The common difference of an arithmetic sequence, as=
 its name suggests, is the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/subtr=
action/">difference</a> between every two of its successive (or consecutive=
) terms. The formula for finding the common difference of an arithmetic seq=
uence is, d =3D a<sub>n</sub> - a<sub>n-1</sub>.</p></div></div></div><div =
